{"lemma":"مَشْرِقُ","slug":"مَشْرِقُ","root":"ش.ر.ق","root_slug":"ش-ر-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ر-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مَشْرِق","root":"شرق","pos":"N","occurrence_count":11},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22206","n22207","n22208","n22211","n22212"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B4%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%82%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"east, direction where the sun rises","examples":[{"text":"قَالَ إِبْرَاهِيمُ فَإِنَّ اللَّهَ يَأْتِي بِالشَّمْسِ مِنَ الْمَشْرِقِ فَأْتِ بِهَا مِنَ الْمَغْرِبِ فَبُهِتَ الَّذِي كَفَرَ","english":"Abraham said, \"God indeed brings the sun from the east; now you bring it from the west.\" Thereat the faithless one was dumbfounded."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"time of sunrise"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"an eastern country"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a sunny place"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Mashriq"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Noun of place from the verb شَرْق (šarq, “east”)."},"ipa":["/maʃ.riq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22206","headword_ar":"مَشْرَقٌ","root":"$rq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next follows."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n22207","headword_ar":"مَشْرِقٌ","root":"$rq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, O, Msb, K,) which by rule should be ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oraqN","text_ar":"مَشْرَقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb,) but this latter is rarely used, (Msb,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quarter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"direction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sunrise;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb;) [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"east,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"orient;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aroqN","text_ar":"شَرْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same; (S, M, O, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mi$oriyqN","text_ar":"مِشْرِيقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Seer, M:) the pl. of the first is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aAriqu","text_ar":"مَشَارِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aroqN","text_ar":"شَرْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oraAqN","text_ar":"اَشْرَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) The dual,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alma$oriqaAni","text_ar":"المَشْرِقَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The place of sunrise of summer and that of winter"},{"kind":"text","text":"[E. 26 degrees N. and E. 26 degrees S. in Central Arabia]. (S, O, TA.) And also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The place of sunrise and the place of sunset;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the east and the west;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (M, O;) the former being thus made predominant because it denotes existence, whereas the latter denotes non-existence: (M:) thus in the saying, (M, O,) in the Kur [xliii. 37], (O,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA layota bayoniY","text_ar":"يَا لَيْتَ بَيْنِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wabayonaka buEoda A@loma$oriqayoni","text_ar":"وَبَيْنَكَ بُعْدَ ا@لْمَشْرِقَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O, would that between me and thee were the distance of the east and the west"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, O.) And [in like manner] one says ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA bayona Al$~aroqayoni","text_ar":"مَا بَيْنَ الشَّرْقَيْنِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is between the place of sunrise and the place of sunset."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oruqapN","text_ar":"مَشْرُقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  The saying, cited by IAar,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"qulotu lisaEodK wahowa biAlA^azoAriqi\n                      \n                     \n                        Ealayoka biAlmaHoDi wabiAlma$aAriqi"},{"kind":"text","text":"he explains as meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I said to Saad, he being at El-Azárik"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a certain water in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAdiyap","text_ar":"بَادِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zrq","text_ar":"زرق"},{"kind":"text","text":")],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Keep thou"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to pure milk, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the sun"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the places of sunshine"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in winter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but [ISd says,] in my opinion,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alma$aAriq","text_ar":"المَشَارِق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu$ar~aqN","text_ar":"مُشَرَّقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to flesh-meat that is “ [cut into strips and] spread in the sun [to dry]; ” and this is confirmed by his saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bAlmHD","text_ar":"بالمحض"},{"kind":"text","text":", each of them being food. (M.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","O","Msb","K","Seer"]},{"entry_id":"n22208","headword_ar":"مُشْرِقٌ","root":"$rq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariqN","text_ar":"شَرِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Entering upon the time of sunrise:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the pl. occurs in this sense in the Kur xv. 73 and xxvi. 60. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n22211","headword_ar":"مُشَرَّقٌ","root":"$rq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of prayer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muSal~FY","text_ar":"مُصَلًّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (As, S, M, Mgh, K;) i. e., in an absolute sense: (TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of prayer of the festival"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEiyd","text_ar":"العِيد"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of prayer of the two festivals:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almu$ar~aqu","text_ar":"المُشَرَّقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the place of prayer of the festival at Mekkeh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the mosque of El-Kheyf."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b2-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"festival"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEiyd","text_ar":"العِيد"},{"kind":"text","text":") [itself]: because the prayer thereon is after the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aroqap","text_ar":"شَرْقَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. the [rising] sun. (M.)       -A2-  Also Flesh-meat ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cut into strips and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spread in the sun"},{"kind":"text","text":"[to dry: see its verb, 2]. (M.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oriqN","text_ar":"مَشْرِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence. ―         -b2-  And A garment, or piece of cloth, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dyed yellow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with saffron:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see, again, its verb: or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dyed with a red colour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.)       -A3-  And a fortress [or a watering-trough or tank (see 2, last sentence,)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plastered with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAruwq","text_ar":"شَارُوق"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","M"]},{"entry_id":"n22212","headword_ar":"مُشَرِّقٌ","root":"$rq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Taking to the direction of the east,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of sunrise:"},{"kind":"text","text":"one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$at~aAna bayona mu$ar~iqK","text_ar":"شَتَّانَ بَيْنَ مُشَرِّقٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wamugar~ibK","text_ar":"وَمُغَرِّبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Different,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"widely different, are one going towards the east and one going towards the west"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}